<li id="cite_note-102"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-102">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><span class="citation Journal"><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://www3.interscience.wiley.com/journal/118669468/abstract">"Abstracts: 36th Annual Meeting of the American College of Veterinary Ophthalmologists, Nashville, TN, USA, October 12–15, 2005"</a>. <i>Veterinary Ophthalmology</i> <b>8</b> (6): 437–450. November 2005. <a href="Digital_object_identifier" title="Digital object identifier">doi</a>:<a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://dx.doi.org/10.1111/j.1463-5224.2005.00442.x">10.1111/j.1463-5224.2005.00442.x</a><span class="printonly">. <a rel="nofollow" class="external free" href="http://www3.interscience.wiley.com/journal/118669468/abstract">http://www3.interscience.wiley.com/journal/118669468/abstract</a></span>. "Based on these data, we conclude that a susceptibility allele for ERU in Appaloosas exists in the MHC region."</span></span></li>
